<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>Inclusive Disjunction</P>
</B>
<P>Let p and q be any two propositions.   The compound proposition &quot;<B>p or q</B>&quot; is called the inclusive disjunction of p and q.   It is denoted as <B>p<FONT FACE="Symbol">&#218;</FONT>
q</B>.</P>

<P>&quot;or&quot; gives a true statement when either of its constituent parts is true.   This is illustrated in the truth table.</P>
