<B><P>Logical Equivalence</P>
</B>
<P>If two propositions p and q have the same truth values in each case, then the two propositions are said to be logically equivalent.   That is p <FONT FACE="Symbol">&#186;</FONT>
 q.</P>

<P>Some logically equivalent propositions are detailed as the &quot;Six Laws of Propositions&quot; on page 9 of your lecture notes.</P>

